        content: "Reactive programming e o paradigma pentru sisteme asincrone, non-blocking.\n\nProject Reactor e libraria reactor folosita de Spring WebFlux:\n- Mono<T>: 0 sau 1 element async\n- Flux<T>: 0 sau N elemente async\n\n```java\nimport reactor.core.publisher.Mono;\nimport reactor.core.publisher.Flux;\n\n// Mono:\nMono<String> hello = Mono.just(\"Hello\");\nMono<User> user = Mono.fromCallable(() -> userService.findById(1L));\n\n// Flux:\nFlux<Integer> numbers = Flux.range(1, 10);\nFlux<String> names = Flux.fromList(List.of(\"Ana\", \"Bob\", \"Carol\"));\n\n// Operatii:\nnumbers\n  .filter(n -> n % 2 == 0)\n  .map(n -> n * n)\n  .take(3)\n  .subscribe(System.out::println); // 4 16 36\n\n// Reactive HTTP call:\nwebClient.get()\n  .uri(\"/users/{id}\", userId)\n  .retrieve()\n  .bodyToMono(User.class)\n  .map(u -> u.getName().toUpperCase());\n```"
