        content: "Circuit Breaker previne cascading failures:\n\n```xml\n<dependency>\n  <groupId>io.github.resilience4j</groupId>\n  <artifactId>resilience4j-spring-boot3</artifactId>\n</dependency>\n```\n\n```yaml\nresilience4j.circuitbreaker:\n  instances:\n    orderService:\n      slidingWindowSize: 10\n      minimumNumberOfCalls: 5\n      failureRateThreshold: 50  # 50% esuate → OPEN\n      waitDurationInOpenState: 30s\n      permittedNumberOfCallsInHalfOpenState: 3\n```\n\n```java\n@Service\npublic class OrderClient {\n\n  @CircuitBreaker(name = \"orderService\", fallbackMethod = \"fallbackGetOrder\")\n  @Retry(name = \"orderService\")\n  @TimeLimiter(name = \"orderService\")\n  public CompletableFuture<Order> getOrder(Long id) {\n    return orderServiceWebClient.get()\n      .uri(\"/orders/\" + id)\n      .retrieve()\n      .bodyToMono(Order.class)\n      .toFuture();\n  }\n\n  public CompletableFuture<Order> fallbackGetOrder(Long id, Exception e) {\n    log.warn(\"Circuit breaker fallback for order {}: {}\", id, e.getMessage());\n    return CompletableFuture.completedFuture(Order.defaultOrder(id));\n  }\n}\n```"
