        content: "Saga Pattern pentru tranzactii distribuite:\n\n```java\n// Orchestrated Saga:\n@Service\npublic class OrderSaga {\n\n  public void createOrder(CreateOrderCommand cmd) {\n    try {\n      // Step 1: Create order\n      Order order = orderService.create(cmd);\n\n      // Step 2: Reserve inventory\n      inventoryClient.reserve(order.getItems());\n\n      // Step 3: Process payment\n      paymentClient.charge(order.getTotalAmount(), order.getCustomerId());\n\n      // Step 4: Confirm\n      orderService.confirm(order.getId());\n\n    } catch (InventoryException e) {\n      // Compensating transaction:\n      orderService.cancel(order.getId());\n      throw new SagaException(\"Not enough inventory\", e);\n\n    } catch (PaymentException e) {\n      // Compensating transactions:\n      inventoryClient.release(order.getItems());\n      orderService.cancel(order.getId());\n      throw new SagaException(\"Payment failed\", e);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSaga choreography (cu Kafka):\n```\nOrderCreated → inventory reserves → InventoryReserved\n→ payment processes → PaymentProcessed\n→ order confirms → OrderConfirmed\n```"
